  "name": "Three Black Crows ADL Strategy",
  "description": "This algorithm identifies the 'Three Black Crows' candlestick pattern on the 1-hour timeframe, signaling potential bearish reversals. It confirms the pattern's validity by checking if the Accumulation/Distribution Line (ADL) is decreasing compared to its previous 10-bar average, generating short entry signals accordingly.",
  "algorithm_type": "CandleStickPattern",
  "prompt": "Design an intermediate-level CandleStickPattern trading algorithm, in Python, that scans for the \"Three Black Crows\" formation on the 1-hour timeframe combined with confirmation from the Accumulation/Distribution Line (ADL). The algorithm should generate a short entry signal whenever a valid Three Black Crows pattern appears and the ADL is decreasing compared to its previous 10 bars average. The trade is exited when either a Hammer or a Bullish Engulfing pattern appears, or if the price increases by more than 1.5% from the short entry. Return all detected signals and trade actions, clearly marking entry and exit points.",
